Chile to Offer Mine Exploration Licenses, Diario Financiero Says

-- B y   J a m e s   A t t w o o d
-- 
2011-03-08T10:38:24Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-08/chile-to-offer-mine-exploration-licenses-diario-financiero-says.html
Chile’s National Mining Company,
known as Enami, is preparing to offer mineral exploration
licenses to private companies, Diario Financiero reported.  The licenses would cover about 200,000 hectares (494,000
acres), the Santiago-based newspaper reported, citing people
familiar with the operation that it didn’t identify.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James Attwood at 
 jattwood3@bloomberg.net  